  "data": {
    "query": "generation interconnection fees milestones",
    "num_results": 5,
    "filters_applied": {
      "market": "ERCOT",
      "data_type": null,
      "year_start": null,
      "year_end": null,
      "range_type": null
    },
    "documents": [
      {
        "id": "c2995e81-75a7-4720-be2c-3b3782fec3d4",
        "score": 0.5831625,
        "text": "The document is an ERCOT fee schedule effective October 1, 2024. It outlines various fees related to ERCOT services, which are non-refundable unless specified by ERCOT Protocols.\n\n1. **Private Wide Area Network (WAN) Fees**:\n   - Based on actual costs for procuring, using, maintaining, and connecting to third-party networks for ERCOT WAN communications.\n   - Initial installation or reconfiguration costs capped at $7,000.\n   - Monthly network management fee capped at $450.\n\n2. **ERCOT Load Resource Registration and Generator Interconnection or Modification Fees**:\n   - $500 for registering a new Load Resource.\n   - Additional $500 if increasing MW size by more than 20% or changing registration type.\n   - Generator registration fees:\n     - $2,300 for Settlement Only Distribution Generators (SODGs).\n     - $8,000 for generators under 10 MW.\n     - $14,000 for generators 10 MW or greater.\n   - $8,000 for changing an existing SODG to a Distribution Generation Resource (DGR).\n\nThe document provides specific fee amounts and conditions for various registration and modification scenarios.",
        "metadata": {
          "drive_path": "gs://tumeai-rag/ERCOT/protocol/ERCOT_Fee_Schedule/page_2.jpg",
          "page_num": 2,
          "title": "ERCOT Fee Schedule",
          "year": "",
          "market": "ERCOT",
          "data_type": "protocol"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "d1db4316-6cd7-4f00-aa3a-acaf1c0c62a1",
        "score": 0.54123086,
        "text": "The document is a fee schedule from ERCOT effective October 1, 2024. It outlines various application and inspection fees related to energy generation and transmission services. Key points include:\n\n1. **Full Interconnection Study (FIS) Application Fee**: \n   - $3,000 for new generators.\n   - $2,700 for modifications to existing generators.\n\n2. **Qualified Scheduling Entity (QSE) and Related Fees**:\n   - $500 per entity for QSE, Sub-QSE, Competitive Retailer (CR), Congestion Revenue Right (CRR) Account Holder, Independent Market Information System Registered Entity (IMRE), Resource Entity, and Transmission/Distribution Service Providers (TDSPs).\n\n3. **Counter-Party Background Check Fee**:\n   - $350 per principal.\n\n4. **Weatherization Inspection Fees**:\n   - Resource Entities and Transmission Service Providers must pay fees for weatherization inspections as per Texas Administrative Code \u00a7 25.55.\n\nThe document specifies that fees are associated with modifications based on the cumulative megawatt (MW) amount of changes submitted within the last 12 months. If modifications are less than 10 MW, the fee is $2,300; if 10 MW or greater, the fee is $14,000.",
        "metadata": {
          "drive_path": "gs://tumeai-rag/ERCOT/protocol/ERCOT_Fee_Schedule/page_3.jpg",
          "page_num": 3,
          "title": "ERCOT Fee Schedule",
          "year": "",
          "market": "ERCOT",
          "data_type": "protocol"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "398acc71-d335-426c-b461-abe5edfd1721",
        "score": 0.48237622,
        "text": "The document page is from the ERCOT Nodal Protocols and focuses on the adjustment period and real-time operations, specifically addressing base point deviation charges for under-generation. It includes:\n\n1. **Definitions**:\n   - **AASP**: Average Aggregated Set Point per QSE per Settlement Point per Resource.\n   - **AVGTG5M**: Average Telemeted Generation for the 5 Minutes.\n   - **OGEN**: Over Generation Volumes per QSE per Settlement Point per Resource.\n   - **PR1**: Price for Set Point Deviation Charge for over-generation.\n   - **K1**: Percentage tolerance for over-generation.\n   - **Q1**: MW tolerance for over-generation.\n   - **N, q, p, r, y, i, wg**: Various parameters related to QSE, Settlement Points, and Intervals.\n\n2. **Base Point Deviation Charge for Under Generation**:\n   - ERCOT charges a QSE for under-generation if metered generation is below certain thresholds.\n   - The charge is based on the lesser of:\n     - 95% of the average of the Base Points in the Settlement Interval adjusted for Ancillary Service deployments.\n     - The average of the Base Points minus five MW.\n   - The formula for calculating the under-generation charge is provided, involving parameters like PR2, RTSPP, KP, and UGEN.\n\nThis section outlines the financial implications and calculations for deviations in generation from expected set points.",
        "metadata": {
          "drive_path": "gs://tumeai-rag/ERCOT/protocol/ERCOT_Nodal_Protocols:_Section_6:_Adjustment_Period_and_Real-Time_Operations/page_268.jpg",
          "page_num": 268,
          "title": "ERCOT Nodal Protocols: Section 6: Adjustment Period and Real-Time Operations",
          "year": "",
          "market": "ERCOT",
          "data_type": "protocol"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "bcb5ea12-5d99-4bdf-b72c-748c41cfa6f3",
        "score": 0.4768918,
        "text": "The document outlines the procedures for charging a Qualified Scheduling Entity (QSE) for over-generation by a Generation Resource, as managed by ERCOT. It specifies that charges apply when over-generation exceeds certain tolerances, which are defined as either 5% of the average Base Points in the Settlement Interval (adjusted for Ancillary Service deployments) or five megawatts above this average.\n\nThe over-generation charge is calculated using the formula:\n\n\\[ BPDAMT_{q,r,p,i} = \\text{Max (PR1, RTSPP}_{p,i}) \\times OGEN_{q,r,p,i} \\]\n\nWhere:\n- \\( OGEN_{q,r,p,i} \\) is the over-generation amount.\n- \\( TWTG_{q,r,p,i} \\) is the time-weighted telemetered generation.\n\nDefinitions for key variables include:\n- **BPDAMT**: Base Point Deviation Charge per QSE per Settlement Point per Resource.\n- **RTSPP**: Real-Time Settlement Point Price per Settlement Point.\n- **TWTG**: Time-Weighted Telemetered Generation per QSE per Settlement Point per Resource.\n\nThe document also notes that certain sections will be deleted upon system implementation.",
        "metadata": {
          "drive_path": "gs://tumeai-rag/ERCOT/protocol/ERCOT_Nodal_Protocols:_Section_6:_Adjustment_Period_and_Real-Time_Operations/page_265.jpg",
          "page_num": 265,
          "title": "ERCOT Nodal Protocols: Section 6: Adjustment Period and Real-Time Operations",
          "year": "",
          "market": "ERCOT",
          "data_type": "protocol"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "b572569f-b267-4c63-aadd-2ab7357bff03",
        "score": 0.46913236,
        "text": "The document page is from the ERCOT Nodal Protocols, dated February 1, 2025, and focuses on Section 6: Adjustment Period and Real-Time Operations. It defines several variables related to energy generation and settlement:\n\n1. **AABP<sub>q,r,p,i</sub> (MW)**: Adjusted Aggregated Base Point per QSE per Settlement Point per Resource, considering Ancillary Service deployments and SCED Dispatch Instructions.\n\n2. **AVGTG5M<sub>q,r,p,i,y</sub> (MW)**: Average Telemeted Generation for the 5 Minutes, representing the average generation for a five-minute interval within a 15-minute Settlement Interval.\n\n3. **OGEN<sub>q,r,p,i</sub> (MWh)**: Over Generation Volumes per QSE per Settlement Point per Resource, indicating the amount over-generated by a resource.\n\n4. **PR1 ($/MWh)**: Price for Base Point Deviation Charge for over-generation when RTSPP is less than $20/MWh, set at $20/MWh.\n\n5. **K1**: Percentage tolerance for over-generation, set at 5%.\n\n6. **Q1 (MW)**: MW tolerance for over-generation, set at five MW.\n\nThe document also includes a section on Set Point Deviation Charge for Over Generation (6.6.5.2), detailing charges for over-generation by resources not classified as Energy Storage Resources (ESRs). It specifies tolerances for over-generation as either 5% of the AASP in the Settlement Interval or five MW above the AASP. The section also references NPRR879, NPRR963, and NPRR1010 for system implementation updates.",
        "metadata": {
          "drive_path": "gs://tumeai-rag/ERCOT/protocol/ERCOT_Nodal_Protocols:_Section_6:_Adjustment_Period_and_Real-Time_Operations/page_266.jpg",
          "page_num": 266,
          "title": "ERCOT Nodal Protocols: Section 6: Adjustment Period and Real-Time Operations",
          "year": "",
          "market": "ERCOT",
          "data_type": "protocol"
        }
      }
    ]
  },
  "error": null,
  "metadata": {}
}

